1
00:02:13,440 --> 00:02:14,840
<i>Do you think</i>

2
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:16,920
<i>love</i>

3
00:02:18,680 --> 00:02:20,280
<i>can kill someone?</i>

4
00:02:23,440 --> 00:02:26,320
SIX YEARS EARLIER

5
00:02:32,880 --> 00:02:34,000
Pie!

6
00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:36,600
That tote bag!

7
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:38,600
Where did you get it from?

8
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:40,960
Faculty giveaway.

9
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:43,880
Pie! Don't you feel itchy
using free stuff?

10
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:45,200
I'm just looking at it

11
00:02:45,280 --> 00:02:48,240
and it already irritates me
and hurts my eyes.

12
00:02:49,680 --> 00:02:51,200
- Give it here.
- Mom.

13
00:02:55,880 --> 00:02:57,280
Use this one.

14
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:59,200
Hurry. Change it.

15
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:02,760
From now on, don't ever let me see you
using a tote bag again.

16
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:04,360
How many times have I told you?

17
00:03:04,440 --> 00:03:06,080
Why do you keep using this stuff?

18
00:03:06,160 --> 00:03:07,960
Hold on.

19
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:10,320
Oh my goodness, Pie!

20
00:03:10,400 --> 00:03:13,680
What's with this shoulder bag?
Why does it look so flimsy?

21
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:16,160
Pie, how can you
even use something like this?

22
00:03:16,240 --> 00:03:18,480
Didn't I tell you
not to use bags like this?

23
00:03:20,800 --> 00:03:22,840
Here, change to this one.

24
00:03:22,920 --> 00:03:25,360
It's authentic and genuine.

25
00:03:25,440 --> 00:03:26,480
I rented it.

26
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:29,080
Here, take it and switch it now.

27
00:03:29,160 --> 00:03:31,760
Mom, does our life
really have to be this extreme?

28
00:03:31,840 --> 00:03:33,920
When someone used to have money

29
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,840
and suddenly doesn't,
people will get suspicious.

30
00:03:36,920 --> 00:03:39,040
You've been living luxuriously
for three years.

31
00:03:39,120 --> 00:03:42,520
You can't suddenly start
looking shabby like this, understand?

32
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:44,160
And besides,

33
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:47,160
several of my friends' children
go to the same university as you.

34
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:48,680
If they start gossiping,

35
00:03:48,760 --> 00:03:50,400
I'll lose face completely, understand?

36
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:51,840
Remember this, Pie.

37
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:55,400
Your good image
is your mother's reputation.

38
00:03:55,480 --> 00:03:58,400
And this, this look.

39
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:00,280
It's so perfect.

40
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:03,240
Wait a second. I'll drive you.

41
00:04:14,040 --> 00:04:15,840
You have to present your project, right?

42
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:20,720
Good luck. I'll pick you up this evening.

43
00:04:21,519 --> 00:04:22,760
Yes, Mom.

44
00:04:26,080 --> 00:04:27,240
- Goodbye.
- Alright.

45
00:04:28,880 --> 00:04:31,080
- Do your best.
- Yes.

46
00:04:33,040 --> 00:04:34,160
Bye.

47
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,120
Is there anything I can help with?

48
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:06,760
Better not. It's physical work.

49
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:09,360
I need something physical to destress.

50
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:14,560
If it's not too difficult, I can help.

51
00:05:14,640 --> 00:05:17,000
Or should I call security
for you, Professor?

52
00:05:19,360 --> 00:05:20,680
I'm not a professor.

53
00:05:22,120 --> 00:05:22,960
The sign says so.

54
00:05:24,640 --> 00:05:25,840
FACULTY AND STAFF PARKING

55
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:29,440
I'm just a special lecturer.

56
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:31,000
I'm only helping a friend.

57
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:34,520
So, are you going to let me help?

58
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:41,400
Then help me get the spare tire.

59
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:43,560
Sure.

60
00:05:52,080 --> 00:05:53,720
That's an expensive bag.

61
00:05:53,800 --> 00:05:55,080
You're just throwing it like that?

62
00:05:55,680 --> 00:05:57,200
It's just a bag.

63
00:05:57,280 --> 00:05:58,480
Should I take it out?

64
00:05:59,520 --> 00:06:00,920
- Go ahead.
- Okay.

65
00:06:02,760 --> 00:06:04,040
Coming through.

66
00:06:11,400 --> 00:06:12,640
All done.

67
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:23,400
Thanks so much for helping.

68
00:06:25,760 --> 00:06:28,440
Honestly, this is my first time
changing a tire too.

69
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:31,840
Come to think of it, it's not that hard.

70
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:34,920
What?

71
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:37,120
Hey.

72
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:42,040
Miss!

73
00:06:42,120 --> 00:06:44,040
The student who helped with the tire!

74
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:47,520
I have to go prepare for class. Excuse me.

75
00:06:59,200 --> 00:07:00,440
Hey, Pie!

76
00:07:00,520 --> 00:07:02,680
What did you do?
Why are you drenched in sweat?

77
00:07:02,760 --> 00:07:04,080
Helped someone change a tire.

78
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:07,680
- You know how to do that?
- No.

79
00:07:07,760 --> 00:07:10,280
- Then why'd you help?
- Stress relief.

80
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:12,320
How?

81
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:16,640
When you feel like screaming but can't,
you have to release it somehow.

82
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:19,520
Not really.

83
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:20,960
How's that related?

84
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:27,120
Like…

85
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:29,600
Imagine

86
00:07:30,560 --> 00:07:34,600
someone making you feel worthless,
like you're not good enough.

87
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:37,920
Helping someone makes you feel valued.

88
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,800
It makes you feel better.

89
00:07:39,880 --> 00:07:43,120
- Whoa, Pie.
- What?

90
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:45,120
You're valuable to me, okay?

91
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:47,960
And you're my best friend.

92
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:49,840
You don't have to help
anyone change tires.

93
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:51,960
- Really?
- Yes.

94
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:58,920
Before you touched my face just now,
did you wash your hands?

95
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:00,440
Sorry.

96
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:08,600
So, wasn't the guy you helped confused
when you suddenly helped him?

97
00:08:11,200 --> 00:08:12,600
He was pretty stunned too.

98
00:08:13,720 --> 00:08:15,480
I bet he was.

99
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:17,320
I wanna see his face.

100
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:19,720
What does he look like?

101
00:08:23,120 --> 00:08:24,240
Is he handsome?

102
00:08:26,720 --> 00:08:30,480
A lot of students are interested in doing
their thesis projects about museums.

103
00:08:30,560 --> 00:08:33,200
So I called you in as an advisor.

104
00:08:33,280 --> 00:08:35,679
Maybe we'll get some recruits
for our company.

105
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:38,240
If any projects look good, guide them.

106
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:41,280
If they're too unrealistic,
just reject them.

107
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:45,320
If I reject them all,
won't your students curse me?

108
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:46,880
Nah.

109
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:48,200
No way they won't.

110
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:51,360
Ready to be cursed?

111
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:54,080
- Bring it on.
- I'll call them.

112
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:56,840
Okay, students! Let's go.

113
00:08:56,920 --> 00:08:59,080
If you're ready, come in. Into the room.

114
00:09:06,160 --> 00:09:07,160
Pun?

115
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:10,640
Wait.

116
00:09:10,720 --> 00:09:12,120
You and Pie know each other?

117
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,120
No.

118
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:15,520
Not really. We just met earlier.

119
00:09:17,720 --> 00:09:18,640
The tire change.

120
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:21,680
The tire!

121
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:24,320
So you're the one Pie helped?

122
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:27,160
LECTURE ROOM 202, FACULTY OF ARCHAEOLOGY

123
00:09:27,240 --> 00:09:30,920
Pie said you looked totally stunned
when she helped you.

124
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:34,080
It was hilarious.

125
00:09:34,160 --> 00:09:35,320
Gossiping about me?

126
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,440
No, not gossiping.

127
00:09:37,520 --> 00:09:39,320
Just telling her what happened.

128
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:41,520
And you and Krarok are…

129
00:09:41,600 --> 00:09:42,720
This is Pun.

130
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:44,680
He's my cousin, my uncle's son.

131
00:09:45,720 --> 00:09:46,560
Nice to meet you.

132
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:51,120
So why are you here?

133
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,160
Wait.

134
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:54,960
The museum consultant
Professor Phupha invited,

135
00:09:55,040 --> 00:09:56,120
is that you?

136
00:09:56,840 --> 00:09:58,080
Yes.

137
00:09:58,160 --> 00:09:59,720
I wanted to surprise you.

138
00:09:59,800 --> 00:10:02,120
Do your presentation well.
I'll be watching.

139
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:05,240
Don't pressure me!
My hands are already sweaty.

140
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:09,680
Just wait till I present.

141
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:11,160
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

142
00:10:12,640 --> 00:10:13,680
Pie.

143
00:10:16,560 --> 00:10:17,600
Your name's Pie, right?

144
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:21,720
Yes. I'm presenting first.

145
00:10:22,760 --> 00:10:24,400
Do your best.

146
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:28,640
Helping me change a tire
doesn't earn you bonus points.

147
00:10:30,680 --> 00:10:31,840
I wasn't expecting any.

148
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:39,760
The Pga K'nyau people
have a distinct clothing culture

149
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:41,760
that expresses their identity.

150
00:10:41,840 --> 00:10:44,120
That's why their weaving knowledge

151
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:46,040
has been passed down
since their ancestors,

152
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:49,760
to make cloth for family use
and for traditional ceremonies.

153
00:10:49,840 --> 00:10:52,680
Hey. Who's the guy
next to Professor Phupha?

154
00:10:52,760 --> 00:10:53,880
He's so handsome.

155
00:10:53,960 --> 00:10:55,200
Insanely handsome.

156
00:10:55,280 --> 00:10:56,480
Handsome with no mercy.

157
00:10:56,560 --> 00:10:59,520
Calm down, Mink. That's my brother.

158
00:11:00,200 --> 00:11:01,600
Stop messing with me, Rok.

159
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:03,560
You're an only child. What brother?

160
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:07,040
He's my cousin, my uncle's son.

161
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:09,640
Pun's friends with Professor Phupha,

162
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:13,320
and he owns an architecture firm
that designs museums.

163
00:11:13,400 --> 00:11:14,920
That's enough. Stop selling.

164
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:17,320
I'll get to know him myself.

165
00:11:21,800 --> 00:11:25,320
Here are examples of woven fabrics
from Huay Tong Kor.

166
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:29,080
Any professors want to add anything
or ask questions?

167
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:30,600
No.

168
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:31,960
No.

169
00:11:32,960 --> 00:11:33,960
Go ahead.

170
00:11:35,560 --> 00:11:36,840
Your project is interesting.

171
00:11:38,720 --> 00:11:42,000
But there are already tons of research
in Thailand on ethnic textiles.

172
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:46,960
How is your project
different from everyone else's?

173
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:50,960
Since there are plenty of sources,

174
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:52,760
did you pick it because it was easy?

175
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:04,840
It's true there's a lot of work
on ethnic groups,

176
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:10,400
but research done as the world
shifts fully into the digital era

177
00:12:10,480 --> 00:12:11,320
doesn't exist yet.

178
00:12:12,360 --> 00:12:15,960
When I finish, I plan to put everything

179
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:19,640
into an e-library, so it's easier
for everyone to access.

180
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:22,600
And I'll link the textiles to society,

181
00:12:22,680 --> 00:12:25,480
politics, and rapidly changing culture.

182
00:12:25,560 --> 00:12:28,120
I'm confident it'll be unique.

183
00:12:33,000 --> 00:12:34,560
Shoot it down.

184
00:12:42,480 --> 00:12:45,840
I'll be looking forward
to your research on these textiles.

185
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:48,160
Thank you.

186
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:50,400
She passes.

187
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:03,200
You were amazing.

188
00:13:03,280 --> 00:13:04,920
Next, please.

189
00:13:07,800 --> 00:13:09,880
- I'm gonna faint.
- Go for it.

190
00:13:15,480 --> 00:13:17,000
You'll see how it's really done.

191
00:13:27,600 --> 00:13:30,040
Hello. I'm Manisa Sorinee.

192
00:13:30,120 --> 00:13:33,600
You can call me Mungmink.

193
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:40,120
I got rejected. This is ridiculous.

194
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:42,360
So many questions.
Who can even answer all that?

195
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:44,720
I stayed up all night. Totally useless.

196
00:13:46,360 --> 00:13:49,640
Hey, everyone got shredded.

197
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:51,800
Only Pie survived.

198
00:13:51,880 --> 00:13:55,480
Honestly, she's been beating you
for four years straight.

199
00:13:55,560 --> 00:13:56,920
What are you saying that for?

200
00:13:57,000 --> 00:13:58,400
Stop talking about her.

201
00:14:00,400 --> 00:14:01,960
Pun praised you like crazy.

202
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:04,240
And you're the only one who passed.

203
00:14:04,320 --> 00:14:07,040
You're gonna get an A++++!

204
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:11,400
Are you okay?

205
00:14:11,480 --> 00:14:13,960
- I'm fine.
- Where did that come from?

206
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:16,080
Mink!

207
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,640
Sorry, Pie.

208
00:14:18,720 --> 00:14:20,320
It slipped.

209
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:21,880
I must've placed it badly.

210
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:24,120
Are you hurt?
Should we go to the hospital?

211
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,960
It's fine. It's just a little.

212
00:14:30,320 --> 00:14:31,800
Be more careful next time, Mink.

213
00:14:31,880 --> 00:14:33,640
Good thing it was a plastic cup.

214
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:36,760
If it was stainless steel,
Pie's head would've split open.

215
00:14:37,640 --> 00:14:39,280
I'm really sorry.

216
00:14:39,360 --> 00:14:41,360
Forget it. Let's go.

217
00:14:42,120 --> 00:14:42,960
Be careful, Mink.

218
00:14:47,040 --> 00:14:48,840
Should've been stainless steel.

219
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:52,600
Did you do that on purpose?

220
00:14:53,600 --> 00:14:56,200
No. Why would I?

221
00:14:56,280 --> 00:14:57,440
Are you crazy?

222
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:05,160
Why does Mink hate me so much?

223
00:15:05,240 --> 00:15:06,560
I don't know.

224
00:15:06,640 --> 00:15:08,880
If she doesn't change,
we'll have to deal with her.

225
00:15:08,960 --> 00:15:10,560
- Tomorrow.
- Deal with her tomorrow?

226
00:15:10,640 --> 00:15:13,080
Number nine! Hey, miss!

227
00:15:13,160 --> 00:15:15,040
Stop! Wait a sec!

228
00:15:15,120 --> 00:15:16,320
You're my ninth person.

229
00:15:16,400 --> 00:15:17,760
I forgot to introduce myself.

230
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:20,440
I'm Tod, from the astrology club.

231
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:23,880
I'm making a free palm reading
for anyone who walks past my camera.

232
00:15:24,840 --> 00:15:26,120
You're really lucky.

233
00:15:26,200 --> 00:15:27,880
Want to join my content?

234
00:15:28,720 --> 00:15:30,920
Do it, just for fun.

235
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:32,240
Ask about your project.

236
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:35,000
See if you'll really get
that A++++ like I said.

237
00:15:35,640 --> 00:15:37,600
- Really?
- Yeah, try it.

238
00:15:37,680 --> 00:15:38,800
Left hand, please.

239
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:51,400
Wow, your love line is really strong.

240
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,600
You're lucky in love.

241
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:56,280
I'm blushing.

242
00:15:56,360 --> 00:15:59,400
- You're gonna get a boyfriend!
- It might not be true.

243
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:02,040
But more than one person will love you.

244
00:16:03,760 --> 00:16:07,760
Popular too! I'm blushing for you!

245
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:08,680
Easy.

246
00:16:09,440 --> 00:16:10,280
But…

247
00:16:11,200 --> 00:16:14,400
the love you receive will be too much,
and it will cause you trouble.

248
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:18,120
Is there a way to fix that?

249
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:19,360
Do we need a ritual?

250
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:21,640
- You mean like spiritual stuff?
- That's right.

251
00:16:21,720 --> 00:16:22,680
- Do we have to do that?
- Spiritual stuff?

252
00:16:23,360 --> 00:16:24,560
We do.

253
00:16:24,640 --> 00:16:25,960
What are you doing?

254
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:28,040
Auntie!

255
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:30,880
Tod, you have to run.

256
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:32,360
- Run where?
- Run!

257
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:34,240
- Run!
- Run, okay!

258
00:16:35,280 --> 00:16:37,320
That's the "too much love" right there.

259
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:39,840
How could you do this?
Letting a man hold your hand

260
00:16:39,920 --> 00:16:42,080
and filming a video, Pie.

261
00:16:42,160 --> 00:16:43,920
Who knows what he'll do with it!

262
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:47,000
Mom, it's just fortune telling.
It's a club activity.

263
00:16:47,080 --> 00:16:47,880
Pie.

264
00:16:47,960 --> 00:16:49,920
Auntie, it's my fault.

265
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:51,520
I'm the one who made her do it.

266
00:16:52,120 --> 00:16:54,640
Rok. Don't cover for Pie.

267
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:58,000
You love your friend and spoil her.

268
00:16:58,080 --> 00:17:00,080
But I won't.

269
00:17:00,160 --> 00:17:02,600
You need to know
what you should and shouldn't do.

270
00:17:02,680 --> 00:17:04,960
- Come on, Pie. We're going home.
- Bye, Auntie.

271
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:06,440
- Bye.
- I'm going. See you.

272
00:17:06,520 --> 00:17:07,359
Text me.

273
00:17:07,440 --> 00:17:08,960
Walk faster, Pie.

274
00:17:12,920 --> 00:17:16,280
There are still kids who let their mom
pick them up at university?

275
00:17:17,520 --> 00:17:19,920
By high school,
kids want to go home by themselves.

276
00:17:20,000 --> 00:17:22,880
You don't see parents
picking them up at university.

277
00:17:22,960 --> 00:17:23,920
Who?

278
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:26,920
Phitpicha Attwijit.

279
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:31,840
Full name and everything.

280
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:34,560
You remember it that clearly. Interested?

281
00:17:35,200 --> 00:17:36,280
She's interesting.

282
00:17:37,320 --> 00:17:38,760
Because she helped you change a tire?

283
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:39,960
Yeah.

284
00:17:40,480 --> 00:17:42,720
And seeing her mom pick her up like that…

285
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:46,000
She feels like two different people.

286
00:17:46,560 --> 00:17:47,400
Interesting.

287
00:17:50,760 --> 00:17:52,600
You're interested.

288
00:17:52,680 --> 00:17:54,400
You've got good taste.

289
00:17:54,480 --> 00:17:55,880
If you like her,

290
00:17:55,960 --> 00:17:57,880
I support you. She's really good.

291
00:17:57,960 --> 00:17:59,240
Come on.

292
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:02,760
Hey, I'm really sorry about earlier.
I didn't mean it.

293
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:05,320
Sorry.

294
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:07,560
I didn't realize you were talking to Rok.

295
00:18:07,640 --> 00:18:09,640
Can I call you Pun, like Rok does?

296
00:18:11,040 --> 00:18:12,200
Sure.

297
00:18:16,680 --> 00:18:18,960
Thank you so much for the advice.

298
00:18:19,040 --> 00:18:20,360
The questions you asked me,

299
00:18:20,440 --> 00:18:22,320
they really broadened my perspective.

300
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:27,680
If Rok and I wanted your help,
would you be available?

301
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:32,680
I'm kind of stuck right now.

302
00:18:32,760 --> 00:18:35,480
I'd love your guidance.

303
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:36,600
Rok too.

304
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:40,280
We'll ask him for advice together.

305
00:18:40,360 --> 00:18:41,400
Is that okay, Pun?

306
00:18:42,560 --> 00:18:43,520
Well…

307
00:18:44,200 --> 00:18:45,240
Alright.

308
00:18:45,320 --> 00:18:46,640
Set it up, Rok.

309
00:18:47,640 --> 00:18:49,200
Thank you, Pun.

310
00:18:53,480 --> 00:18:55,520
Hey, Mink! Wait!

311
00:18:57,200 --> 00:18:59,000
Why suddenly consult Pun
about your project?

312
00:18:59,080 --> 00:18:59,880
Planning something?

313
00:18:59,960 --> 00:19:02,400
I just think your brother's cute.

314
00:19:02,480 --> 00:19:05,560
Cool and stylish. Totally my type.

315
00:19:05,640 --> 00:19:08,080
All those seniors and juniors you dated,

316
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:09,200
weren't they your type?

317
00:19:09,280 --> 00:19:11,280
Those don't count.

318
00:19:11,360 --> 00:19:13,920
With your brother, I'm serious.

319
00:19:15,040 --> 00:19:17,440
And don't invite Pie.

320
00:19:18,480 --> 00:19:21,360
Why? Afraid she'll steal the spotlight?

321
00:19:22,800 --> 00:19:25,560
Pie already passed her project.
Why invite her?

322
00:19:27,480 --> 00:19:29,800
Set it up with just you and me.

323
00:19:29,880 --> 00:19:31,480
Just the two of us. Okay?

324
00:19:47,680 --> 00:19:50,160
You really have to go
to Mae Hong Son for this project?

325
00:19:50,760 --> 00:19:52,440
Can't you do it somewhere closer?

326
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:54,960
I told you, Mom.

327
00:19:55,040 --> 00:19:57,640
To study tribal Thai textiles,
you have to go there

328
00:19:57,720 --> 00:19:59,120
to see the real thing.

329
00:20:01,520 --> 00:20:03,600
I don't even want you to go.

330
00:20:03,680 --> 00:20:07,240
If I weren't renovating the house,
I'd follow you.

331
00:20:07,760 --> 00:20:10,320
Who knows if the people there
are trustworthy.

332
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:13,120
Mom.

333
00:20:14,040 --> 00:20:15,680
You have the hotel's number.

334
00:20:15,760 --> 00:20:16,800
You can call anytime.

335
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:19,080
Don't worry.

336
00:20:19,160 --> 00:20:20,760
Rok's going with me.

337
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:27,200
Do you think your mom
will find out we lied?

338
00:20:27,280 --> 00:20:29,320
I don't want to get beheaded.

339
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:32,160
If you don't talk, and I don't talk,
how would she know?

340
00:20:33,920 --> 00:20:35,760
Your mom's not like other moms.

341
00:20:35,840 --> 00:20:37,520
She catches on to everything.

342
00:20:37,600 --> 00:20:39,640
Are you sure you're really going?

343
00:20:40,560 --> 00:20:42,120
I have to go.

344
00:20:42,640 --> 00:20:45,000
This is my last chance in life

345
00:20:45,080 --> 00:20:48,480
to do something I truly want,
something I love.

346
00:20:49,080 --> 00:20:51,080
It's just three months.

347
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:53,360
After I graduate and start working,

348
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:55,160
I won't get this chance again.

349
00:20:55,240 --> 00:20:58,880
Please, please, please. Please help me.

350
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:02,440
Please, Rok. You're my best friend.

351
00:21:03,560 --> 00:21:05,520
Alright, alright.

352
00:21:05,600 --> 00:21:06,880
I'll help.

353
00:21:07,880 --> 00:21:08,800
Yes!

354
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:13,200
Hey! Over here!

355
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:14,640
- Hey!
- That's Rok over there.

356
00:21:14,720 --> 00:21:16,160
I'm coming!

357
00:21:18,720 --> 00:21:20,920
- Hello, Auntie.
- Hello.

358
00:21:22,440 --> 00:21:23,600
Did you come alone?

359
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:26,920
Your mom usually sends you off,
even for short trips.

360
00:21:29,840 --> 00:21:31,480
She did, and she already left.

361
00:21:31,560 --> 00:21:33,200
She had a meeting this morning.

362
00:21:33,280 --> 00:21:34,360
I see.

363
00:21:35,480 --> 00:21:38,160
And that's all you're bringing?

364
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:42,240
Her things are with mine.

365
00:21:42,320 --> 00:21:45,320
It's easier to carry together.

366
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:47,680
That makes sense.

367
00:21:48,280 --> 00:21:50,800
Come on. Let's go check in
before you miss your flight.

368
00:21:50,880 --> 00:21:52,040
Mom, no need.

369
00:21:52,120 --> 00:21:53,600
We can check in online ourselves.

370
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:57,520
Mom, the painters are coming today,

371
00:21:57,600 --> 00:21:58,960
and the sofa delivery too.

372
00:21:59,040 --> 00:22:00,800
- Right.
- If you don't inspect it yourself

373
00:22:00,880 --> 00:22:03,800
and something's wrong,
you'll have to deal with returns.

374
00:22:03,880 --> 00:22:06,600
You should go. We'll handle this.

375
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:10,000
You're right. I have to check it myself.

376
00:22:10,080 --> 00:22:12,600
Can't trust workers with things like that.

377
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:13,560
Exactly.

378
00:22:14,360 --> 00:22:15,240
Bye, Mom.

379
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:20,400
My dear Pie.

380
00:22:23,640 --> 00:22:25,840
- Travel safely.
- Yes.

381
00:22:25,920 --> 00:22:29,720
- When you get there, don't forget…
- Call you every day.

382
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:31,040
I won't forget.

383
00:22:31,840 --> 00:22:32,760
Pie.

384
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:38,360
Focus on your work.

385
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:39,800
And when you're done,

386
00:22:39,880 --> 00:22:41,680
come straight home, understand?

387
00:22:41,760 --> 00:22:43,880
- Take good care of yourselves.
- Yes.

388
00:22:43,960 --> 00:22:45,920
- Bye, Mom.
- Bye.

389
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:47,200
- Bye, Auntie.
- Bye.

390
00:22:47,280 --> 00:22:48,640
Drive safe.

391
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:51,600
- I'm going now.
- Bye!

392
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:54,560
- Bye, Mom!
- Bye.

393
00:23:14,400 --> 00:23:16,920
Since you've decided to lie to your mom,

394
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:19,480
you better live it up, Pie.

395
00:23:19,560 --> 00:23:20,760
Come here. One hug.

396
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:24,880
Thanks, really.

397
00:23:24,960 --> 00:23:27,240
I'm going to make
these three months count,

398
00:23:27,320 --> 00:23:29,640
more than the past 21 years of my life.

399
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:32,680
Once I graduate and start working for Mom,

400
00:23:32,760 --> 00:23:35,240
I won't get this chance again.

401
00:23:35,320 --> 00:23:37,160
- Make it worth it, okay?
- Yeah.

402
00:23:37,240 --> 00:23:40,880
When you come back,
I've got someone to introduce you to.

403
00:23:40,960 --> 00:23:42,080
Who?

404
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:44,360
You'll find out when you're back.

405
00:23:45,120 --> 00:23:45,960
Go on.

406
00:23:46,040 --> 00:23:47,080
Okay.

407
00:23:47,680 --> 00:23:50,880
- Love you, Rok.
- Love you too.

408
00:23:52,320 --> 00:23:53,280
Thanks.

409
00:23:53,360 --> 00:23:54,960
- Bye!
- See you in three months!

410
00:23:55,560 --> 00:23:56,720
Get home safe.

411
00:23:56,800 --> 00:23:59,400
- Text me.
- Yeah. See you.

412
00:24:01,200 --> 00:24:02,840
Bye!

413
00:24:26,320 --> 00:24:27,600
Excuse me.

414
00:24:28,600 --> 00:24:29,600
ROW 17

415
00:24:40,040 --> 00:24:41,000
Sir?

416
00:24:42,880 --> 00:24:44,040
Sir?

417
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:47,360
Are you in the wrong seat?

418
00:24:48,120 --> 00:24:49,640
Are you sure you're not mistaken?

419
00:24:51,200 --> 00:24:53,760
No. This is 17A.

420
00:24:58,560 --> 00:25:00,960
Sorry. I'll move.

421
00:25:01,040 --> 00:25:01,920
Thank you.

422
00:25:09,480 --> 00:25:11,320
I'm not feeling well. I might throw up.

423
00:25:11,920 --> 00:25:13,040
Just climb over me.

424
00:25:13,120 --> 00:25:14,120
Huh?

425
00:25:15,680 --> 00:25:17,840
Climb over me. I don't mind.

426
00:25:20,360 --> 00:25:21,560
Okay.

427
00:25:42,400 --> 00:25:43,440
Are you drunk?

428
00:25:46,680 --> 00:25:48,440
Don't tell anyone I'm drunk.

429
00:25:48,520 --> 00:25:50,160
I told them I'm allergic to the weather.

430
00:25:50,720 --> 00:25:51,840
I'm going to sleep.

431
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:22,080
Hold on! That's my water.

432
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:24,320
What are you talking about? This is mine.

433
00:26:25,080 --> 00:26:28,280
No. Yours is here. I moved it.

434
00:26:29,040 --> 00:26:30,480
Take this one.

435
00:26:30,560 --> 00:26:33,080
No! You already drank from it.

436
00:26:34,280 --> 00:26:35,160
Then take this.

437
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:38,560
You've had both.
Keep them. I don't want them.

438
00:26:40,320 --> 00:26:43,280
I only took a sip. You sure?

439
00:26:43,360 --> 00:26:44,840
No.

440
00:26:48,160 --> 00:26:49,240
Suit yourself.

441
00:26:49,320 --> 00:26:51,080
Take it if you change your mind.

442
00:27:17,280 --> 00:27:18,080
THA PHAE GATE

443
00:27:19,240 --> 00:27:21,080
Hey, I'm in Chiang Mai.

444
00:27:21,160 --> 00:27:24,400
On a red truck heading to the bus station.
The weather's amazing.

445
00:27:24,920 --> 00:27:28,200
Don't get too distracted.

446
00:27:28,280 --> 00:27:30,280
Watch yourself.

447
00:27:30,360 --> 00:27:32,840
How was the trip?

448
00:27:33,720 --> 00:27:36,440
Not great. Sat next to a rude guy.

449
00:27:36,520 --> 00:27:39,360
He was drunk, in the wrong seat,

450
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:43,120
made me climb over him.
Even grabbed the wrong water bottle.

451
00:27:43,200 --> 00:27:46,080
Come on. It's fine.

452
00:27:46,160 --> 00:27:48,200
You won't see him again.

453
00:27:48,720 --> 00:27:50,080
Yeah.

454
00:27:50,160 --> 00:27:52,520
I hope I never run
into someone like that again.

455
00:27:54,600 --> 00:27:56,600
That's it. Bye.

456
00:27:57,800 --> 00:27:59,200
Bye.

457
00:28:07,040 --> 00:28:08,120
Seriously?

458
00:28:08,200 --> 00:28:10,560
UHT MILK

459
00:28:11,240 --> 00:28:13,480
There's really no other bus?

460
00:28:13,560 --> 00:28:15,760
I told you, they're all full.

461
00:28:15,840 --> 00:28:17,720
Next one's in three hours.

462
00:28:17,800 --> 00:28:21,960
This truck was chartered
to deliver donations to Mae Hong Son.

463
00:28:22,040 --> 00:28:24,760
This guy missed his bus too.

464
00:28:24,840 --> 00:28:26,040
You going?

465
00:28:26,120 --> 00:28:28,360
If you won't, wait three hours.

466
00:28:30,840 --> 00:28:33,160
Can she tag along?

467
00:28:33,240 --> 00:28:34,720
If there's room, hop in.

468
00:28:34,800 --> 00:28:36,040
Thank you.

469
00:28:37,440 --> 00:28:40,000
You going? Don't think too long.
We're leaving.

470
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:17,880
What's wrong?

471
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:19,160
I'm drunk.

472
00:29:19,680 --> 00:29:21,400
Obviously.

473
00:29:22,400 --> 00:29:25,040
Not that kind. Carsick. I'm gonna puke.

474
00:29:27,760 --> 00:29:30,640
Hey, wait! Don't puke yet!

475
00:29:30,720 --> 00:29:32,920
Hold on! Driver!

476
00:29:33,520 --> 00:29:36,160
Please pull over! He's going to throw up!

477
00:29:36,240 --> 00:29:37,680
Please stop!

478
00:29:37,760 --> 00:29:39,840
Please stop! Please!

479
00:29:39,920 --> 00:29:42,960
Please pull over! He's going to throw up!

480
00:30:13,440 --> 00:30:14,400
Thank you.

481
00:30:15,520 --> 00:30:17,600
So you can speak nicely too?

482
00:30:19,240 --> 00:30:20,840
Can you keep going?

483
00:30:21,560 --> 00:30:22,640
I'm fine.

484
00:30:23,240 --> 00:30:25,160
You don't look fine.

485
00:30:25,240 --> 00:30:27,200
Want a motion sickness pill?

486
00:30:27,280 --> 00:30:28,280
It's okay.

487
00:30:29,280 --> 00:30:30,440
I threw up already.

488
00:30:30,960 --> 00:30:32,240
Should be fine.

489
00:30:34,840 --> 00:30:35,720
You sure?

490
00:30:38,440 --> 00:30:40,320
- Let's go.
- Okay.

491
00:31:11,960 --> 00:31:13,560
Again? Wait!

492
00:31:13,640 --> 00:31:15,200
- Here.
- Huh?

493
00:31:15,280 --> 00:31:16,640
You gonna puke in his truck?

494
00:31:17,440 --> 00:31:18,440
Hook it on your ears.

495
00:31:19,560 --> 00:31:20,640
So it won't spill.

496
00:31:21,680 --> 00:31:23,160
I'm not a kid.

497
00:31:26,240 --> 00:31:28,600
Hey, want some inhaler?

498
00:31:29,320 --> 00:31:30,480
Take the pills.

499
00:31:30,560 --> 00:31:31,720
Water.

500
00:31:34,400 --> 00:31:35,440
Why do you have everything?

501
00:31:35,520 --> 00:31:37,080
For people who don't have anything.

502
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:41,920
Take it, so we don't have to stop again.
I don't want to arrive late.

503
00:31:47,760 --> 00:31:51,720
I've got gum and mints too. Help yourself.

504
00:31:52,240 --> 00:31:53,240
Here.

505
00:32:56,040 --> 00:32:58,480
PIE PHITPICHA ATTWIJIT

506
00:33:00,040 --> 00:33:01,840
Aunt Saen from Saensuk Homestay, right?

507
00:33:02,680 --> 00:33:05,040
- Hello.
- Hello, Miss Pie.

508
00:33:05,120 --> 00:33:07,120
You don't have to call me "miss."
Pie is fine.

509
00:33:07,880 --> 00:33:08,800
Alright then, Pie it is.

510
00:33:08,880 --> 00:33:10,160
How was your trip?

511
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:13,240
Don't even ask, Aunt Saen.
It's a miracle I made it here alive.

512
00:33:14,320 --> 00:33:15,400
Why's that?

513
00:33:16,080 --> 00:33:18,600
I ran into this drunk guy.

514
00:33:18,680 --> 00:33:20,440
He was wasted
from the plane to the red truck.

515
00:33:20,520 --> 00:33:24,200
He kept throwing up, so we had to stop.
Otherwise, it would've been all over me.

516
00:33:24,280 --> 00:33:26,640
Drunk people are really the worst.

517
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:28,240
Exactly.

518
00:33:29,120 --> 00:33:30,880
Here comes that rascal, my nephew.

519
00:33:31,480 --> 00:33:33,760
Win! Over here!

520
00:33:35,120 --> 00:33:36,560
Hi, Auntie.

521
00:33:36,640 --> 00:33:38,000
You're so slow.

522
00:33:38,640 --> 00:33:39,840
You've got to be kidding me.

523
00:33:45,040 --> 00:33:46,840
Don't tell me…

524
00:33:47,640 --> 00:33:48,600
Yes, Auntie.

525
00:33:51,320 --> 00:33:52,160
Win!

526
00:33:53,280 --> 00:33:54,680
- Sorry.
- It's alright.

527
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:07,320
Oh my gosh, Win!

528
00:34:07,400 --> 00:34:09,960
You knew you had to travel,
and you still went drinking.

529
00:34:10,040 --> 00:34:12,360
And when you're drunk,
you don't take medicine.

530
00:34:13,040 --> 00:34:14,960
- What's wrong?!
- He's going to throw up again!

531
00:34:15,040 --> 00:34:16,360
- Hang on!
- Aunt Saen, pull over!

532
00:34:16,440 --> 00:34:17,840
Go ahead!

533
00:34:19,880 --> 00:34:21,480
Are you done emptying your guts?

534
00:34:21,560 --> 00:34:22,719
Serves you right.

535
00:34:24,560 --> 00:34:26,480
That's what you get for drinking.

536
00:35:03,960 --> 00:35:04,960
How are you doing, Win?

537
00:35:05,040 --> 00:35:06,760
Is everything settled?

538
00:35:09,200 --> 00:35:10,160
Yes.

539
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:12,560
I've taken care of the house.

540
00:35:13,600 --> 00:35:16,320
Anything I couldn't sell, I donated.

541
00:35:18,840 --> 00:35:20,840
I meant your heart.

542
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:23,160
Have you come to terms with it yet?

543
00:35:30,160 --> 00:35:31,480
Some days I have.

544
00:35:32,280 --> 00:35:33,760
Some days I haven't.

545
00:35:35,480 --> 00:35:38,200
I don't know
how to stop thinking about it.

546
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:42,360
Who would've thought

547
00:35:43,280 --> 00:35:45,400
that someone you saw in the morning

548
00:35:47,040 --> 00:35:49,680
would be gone forever by evening.

549
00:35:51,400 --> 00:35:53,640
Come on. Don't overthink it.

550
00:35:54,160 --> 00:35:56,520
Your parents are at peace now.

551
00:36:10,840 --> 00:36:11,920
Were you eavesdropping?

552
00:36:18,320 --> 00:36:19,600
I wasn't eavesdropping.

553
00:36:19,680 --> 00:36:21,320
I just had something to ask.

554
00:36:21,400 --> 00:36:23,080
I happened to overhear it.

555
00:36:24,840 --> 00:36:27,640
Aunt Saen,
I'm really sorry for being rude.

556
00:36:29,240 --> 00:36:32,040
I can't find the phone.
I wanted to ask where it is.

557
00:36:32,640 --> 00:36:35,320
I need to call home at 8 p.m.

558
00:36:51,720 --> 00:36:53,640
Write the time down in the logbook.

559
00:36:53,720 --> 00:36:55,320
My aunt collects at month's end.

560
00:36:55,400 --> 00:36:56,600
Okay.

561
00:37:04,360 --> 00:37:05,720
Are you going to listen too?

562
00:37:06,440 --> 00:37:08,160
I'm just here to lock the phone.

563
00:37:08,240 --> 00:37:10,320
I don't eavesdrop. Unlike some people.

564
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:20,840
Hello?

565
00:37:20,920 --> 00:37:23,400
Mom, it's me.

566
00:37:23,480 --> 00:37:26,360
Pie! Why couldn't I reach you?

567
00:37:26,440 --> 00:37:28,840
Mom, there's no mobile signal here.

568
00:37:28,920 --> 00:37:30,200
We can only use a landline.

569
00:37:30,280 --> 00:37:31,800
What do you mean?

570
00:37:31,880 --> 00:37:33,400
Is it really that remote?

571
00:37:33,480 --> 00:37:35,600
<i>What if something happens?</i>

572
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:38,960
Nothing will happen, Mom.
Everyone here is kind.

573
00:37:39,040 --> 00:37:41,320
- Women or men?
- Women.

574
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:43,200
An auntie.

575
00:37:45,000 --> 00:37:46,280
There are no men here.

576
00:37:47,240 --> 00:37:48,640
<i>That's good.</i>

577
00:37:48,720 --> 00:37:49,720
<i>Pie.</i>

578
00:37:49,800 --> 00:37:53,160
<i>Don't forget to call me</i>
<i>every day at 8 p.m.</i>

579
00:37:53,240 --> 00:37:54,920
I'll be waiting, understand?

580
00:37:55,680 --> 00:37:57,120
Yes, Mom.

581
00:37:57,200 --> 00:38:00,720
And if you don't call,
I'll come there myself.

582
00:38:00,800 --> 00:38:02,720
Mom, I understand.

583
00:38:02,800 --> 00:38:05,480
I'll report to you every day.

584
00:38:06,160 --> 00:38:07,280
<i>Okay.</i>

585
00:38:08,120 --> 00:38:11,760
Yes, Mom. Goodbye.

586
00:38:24,800 --> 00:38:27,840
Wait. I thought you said
you don't eavesdrop.

587
00:38:32,760 --> 00:38:33,800
I'm here to lock the phone.

588
00:38:35,080 --> 00:38:36,200
I've said it already.

589
00:38:39,200 --> 00:38:40,400
Are you done?

590
00:38:41,080 --> 00:38:42,160
Not yet.

591
00:38:42,920 --> 00:38:43,880
Then write it down.

592
00:39:06,280 --> 00:39:08,120
Be careful. The floor's uneven.

593
00:39:10,040 --> 00:39:11,200
Thank you.

594
00:39:13,680 --> 00:39:15,040
So you can speak nicely too?

595
00:39:17,160 --> 00:39:18,000
Here.

596
00:39:18,080 --> 00:39:19,240
Thank you.

597
00:39:20,720 --> 00:39:22,600
So you can speak nicely too?

598
00:39:26,720 --> 00:39:27,680
Are you being sarcastic?

599
00:39:30,440 --> 00:39:32,200
Just copying someone.

600
00:39:34,560 --> 00:39:35,800
Hang on.

601
00:39:46,800 --> 00:39:48,280
I'm sorry

602
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:50,760
about earlier on the plane.

603
00:39:51,280 --> 00:39:53,280
I thought you were

604
00:39:53,360 --> 00:39:56,840
just some rude and thoughtless drunk.

605
00:40:03,600 --> 00:40:06,080
But now I understand
why you were that drunk.

606
00:40:10,240 --> 00:40:11,640
I'm sorry…

607
00:40:13,320 --> 00:40:14,800
about your parents.

608
00:40:20,240 --> 00:40:21,160
Thank you.

609
00:40:29,720 --> 00:40:31,160
Don't be so formal.

610
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:33,960
Just call me Win.

611
00:40:34,880 --> 00:40:35,720
Okay.

612
00:40:36,640 --> 00:40:37,800
So…

613
00:40:38,520 --> 00:40:40,960
Nice to meet you, Win.

614
00:40:41,040 --> 00:40:43,320
Nice to meet you, Pie.

615
00:41:26,040 --> 00:41:27,400
<i>What's she doing here?</i>

616
00:41:27,480 --> 00:41:30,800
She's doing a project
about tribal woven textiles.

617
00:41:30,880 --> 00:41:33,760
She rented a room for three months.

618
00:41:34,280 --> 00:41:37,640
<i>Looks like a proper young lady,</i>
<i>but she came up the mountain alone.</i>

619
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:51,000
Here it is.

620
00:41:51,080 --> 00:41:54,080
Gold brocade with a Garuda
grabbing a Naga pattern.

621
00:41:54,160 --> 00:41:56,080
It's beautiful, Dech.

622
00:41:56,160 --> 00:41:59,120
The most exquisite of all brocades.

623
00:42:00,360 --> 00:42:02,280
You know, they use real gold,

624
00:42:02,360 --> 00:42:04,840
spun into golden silk threads,

625
00:42:04,920 --> 00:42:08,440
and weave it together with silk.

626
00:42:08,520 --> 00:42:10,400
The center section

627
00:42:10,480 --> 00:42:13,720
is called the body of the cloth.
That's where the Garuda and Naga appear.

628
00:42:13,800 --> 00:42:16,560
That's how it got its name.

629
00:42:16,640 --> 00:42:19,240
- How much?
- Five hundred thousand.

630
00:42:20,480 --> 00:42:21,320
That's not expensive.

631
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:23,000
Very cheap.

632
00:42:23,080 --> 00:42:25,560
Let me tell you, this piece

633
00:42:25,640 --> 00:42:29,840
took two years to complete,
from the detailing to the patterns.

634
00:42:29,920 --> 00:42:32,560
- Wow.
- You know, if you break it down,

635
00:42:32,640 --> 00:42:35,720
the artisans only earn
a few tens of thousands per month.

636
00:42:35,800 --> 00:42:39,080
For craftsmanship at this level,

637
00:42:39,160 --> 00:42:41,160
it's absolutely worth it.

638
00:42:42,800 --> 00:42:43,800
So, are you selling it?

639
00:42:43,880 --> 00:42:45,000
No.

640
00:42:45,080 --> 00:42:45,920
Not selling.

641
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:48,400
Do you know how hard it was to get this?

642
00:42:48,480 --> 00:42:50,680
I walked all over Surin for it.

643
00:42:51,400 --> 00:42:53,920
Even if we're best friends,
I won't sell it.

644
00:42:54,000 --> 00:42:55,560
Then why show it off?

645
00:42:55,640 --> 00:42:57,320
To make you jealous.

646
00:42:57,400 --> 00:42:58,880
Well, you succeeded.

647
00:43:05,240 --> 00:43:08,800
Pun, call your dad and see where he is.

648
00:43:08,880 --> 00:43:10,400
Uncle Dech is heading home.

649
00:43:10,480 --> 00:43:11,600
Okay.

650
00:43:13,640 --> 00:43:16,680
My niece will be here in ten minutes.

651
00:43:16,760 --> 00:43:19,800
If your husband's not back yet,
I'm leaving first.

652
00:43:19,880 --> 00:43:21,480
Your niece?

653
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:23,720
The one you raised like your own?

654
00:43:23,800 --> 00:43:26,640
The one whose parents passed away?

655
00:43:27,360 --> 00:43:29,320
Yes, the only one.

656
00:43:29,400 --> 00:43:32,480
I've raised her since primary school.
She's about to graduate now.

657
00:43:32,560 --> 00:43:34,560
And I'm not bragging,

658
00:43:34,640 --> 00:43:37,000
but her father's assets,
her mother's assets,

659
00:43:37,080 --> 00:43:40,120
and mine as well,
she'll live comfortably for life.

660
00:43:40,200 --> 00:43:41,200
Well.

661
00:43:41,280 --> 00:43:42,720
Same as Pun.

662
00:43:42,800 --> 00:43:45,920
Only child, only grandchild.
The family fortune came to me,

663
00:43:46,000 --> 00:43:48,160
but eventually,
it will all go to him anyway.

664
00:43:48,240 --> 00:43:51,000
Whoever marries him
better be chosen carefully.

665
00:43:51,080 --> 00:43:53,560
Otherwise, we might end up
with a terrible daughter-in-law.

666
00:43:53,640 --> 00:43:54,480
Exactly.

667
00:43:54,560 --> 00:43:55,560
Mom.

668
00:43:56,360 --> 00:43:58,840
Dad says he won't be home
for another two hours.

669
00:44:00,160 --> 00:44:01,040
Your father.

670
00:44:01,120 --> 00:44:03,560
Every time he goes golfing,
he disappears all day.

671
00:44:03,640 --> 00:44:05,320
Training for the Olympics or what?

672
00:44:06,280 --> 00:44:09,080
Anyway, how long are you staying
this time after Nepal?

673
00:44:09,160 --> 00:44:10,800
For a while.

674
00:44:10,880 --> 00:44:13,200
Mink's graduating soon.
She wants me to invest with her.

675
00:44:14,040 --> 00:44:15,560
Mink? Who?

676
00:44:15,640 --> 00:44:18,840
My niece, Mungmink.

677
00:44:20,920 --> 00:44:22,200
Her name's Mungmink?

678
00:44:33,960 --> 00:44:35,360
Pun?

679
00:44:39,040 --> 00:44:40,320
This is a coincidence, right?

680
00:44:49,920 --> 00:44:51,760
This is totally fate.

681
00:44:51,840 --> 00:44:53,880
What fate?

682
00:44:53,960 --> 00:44:57,520
Fate that Uncle Dech
became friends with Pun's mom

683
00:44:57,600 --> 00:45:00,200
and that you, my best friend,

684
00:45:00,280 --> 00:45:01,920
ended up being his cousin.

685
00:45:02,000 --> 00:45:03,000
Perfect match.

686
00:45:05,280 --> 00:45:07,640
Don't get ahead of yourself, Mink.

687
00:45:08,280 --> 00:45:10,800
Take it slow. Don't get your hopes up.

688
00:45:11,960 --> 00:45:14,520
What, does that mean
Pun's already married?

689
00:45:14,600 --> 00:45:15,920
- No.
- Girlfriend?

690
00:45:16,000 --> 00:45:17,640
- No.
- Is he gay?

691
00:45:17,720 --> 00:45:19,040
No!

692
00:45:19,120 --> 00:45:20,880
Then I'm not holding back.

693
00:45:20,960 --> 00:45:22,560
I'm going all in.

694
00:45:35,760 --> 00:45:36,600
Aunt Saen!

695
00:45:36,680 --> 00:45:38,160
Yes?

696
00:45:38,240 --> 00:45:40,800
I'm going to the Pga K'nyau village
to gather information.

697
00:45:40,880 --> 00:45:42,800
I heard you have bicycles
for guests to use.

698
00:45:42,880 --> 00:45:44,240
May I borrow one?

699
00:45:44,320 --> 00:45:46,600
- Of course.
- Thank you.

700
00:45:46,680 --> 00:45:48,880
- Wait, Pie!
- Yes?

701
00:45:48,960 --> 00:45:51,320
I don't think
you should ride there. It's far.

702
00:45:52,360 --> 00:45:54,080
The road's rough.

703
00:45:54,160 --> 00:45:56,640
Lots of curves, uphill and downhill.

704
00:45:58,080 --> 00:45:59,760
If you're not familiar,
you might get lost.

705
00:45:59,840 --> 00:46:02,600
Let Win drive you instead.

706
00:46:03,240 --> 00:46:04,320
Huh?

707
00:46:09,920 --> 00:46:11,760
It's okay, Aunt Saen.

708
00:46:12,360 --> 00:46:15,400
I can go by myself. Life is an adventure.

709
00:46:17,840 --> 00:46:20,040
Okay.

710
00:46:20,120 --> 00:46:23,000
- Go on then.
- Alright, I'm off.

711
00:46:23,600 --> 00:46:25,480
- Ride carefully!
- Yes.

712
00:47:01,360 --> 00:47:02,680
- Just a second.
- Okay.

713
00:47:02,760 --> 00:47:03,960
- Hang in there.
- It's okay.

714
00:47:04,040 --> 00:47:05,080
Here.

715
00:47:09,760 --> 00:47:12,680
Life is an adventure, right?

716
00:47:13,880 --> 00:47:15,840
You should rest today.

717
00:47:15,920 --> 00:47:17,280
I'll drive you tomorrow.

718
00:47:17,360 --> 00:47:20,320
No, it's fine. I want to ride myself.

719
00:47:20,400 --> 00:47:22,040
I'll try again tomorrow.

720
00:47:22,120 --> 00:47:23,240
Aren't you afraid of dying?

721
00:47:23,320 --> 00:47:25,920
If you're always afraid,
how are you going to live?

722
00:47:26,800 --> 00:47:29,920
If you're not afraid of anything,
you might die before you live.

723
00:47:30,000 --> 00:47:31,680
You little brat!

724
00:47:31,760 --> 00:47:33,640
That's enough!

725
00:47:34,400 --> 00:47:36,720
You're great at saying hurtful things.

726
00:47:36,800 --> 00:47:39,800
Aunt Saen, I'm not discouraged at all.

727
00:47:39,880 --> 00:47:42,480
I'm totally fine. I'll keep going.

728
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:44,200
Just a little fall.

729
00:47:44,800 --> 00:47:46,760
It won't kill me.

730
00:47:57,000 --> 00:47:59,000
I've thought of five project ideas.

731
00:47:59,080 --> 00:48:00,840
I'm deciding which one to choose.

732
00:48:03,520 --> 00:48:04,600
Pick something different.

733
00:48:04,680 --> 00:48:07,600
When you presented, it lacked vision.

734
00:48:11,560 --> 00:48:14,920
Let me organize each concept first,

735
00:48:15,000 --> 00:48:16,400
then can I call you for advice?

736
00:48:17,280 --> 00:48:18,400
Sure.

737
00:48:18,480 --> 00:48:20,840
You too, Rok.

738
00:48:20,920 --> 00:48:24,560
Come up with a new topic and call me.

739
00:48:24,640 --> 00:48:25,840
Make it quick.

740
00:48:26,800 --> 00:48:28,360
Others have already started.

741
00:48:29,080 --> 00:48:30,400
Even Phitpicha.

742
00:48:30,920 --> 00:48:32,680
Wow, Pun.

743
00:48:32,760 --> 00:48:35,840
Using her full name like that?
You can just call her Pie.

744
00:48:37,000 --> 00:48:39,280
They're not close.
Why would he use her nickname?

745
00:48:41,880 --> 00:48:43,240
I can use her nickname.

746
00:48:44,200 --> 00:48:46,560
How's Pie? She went
to Mae Hong Son, right?

747
00:48:46,640 --> 00:48:49,520
Yeah. But I haven't talked to her.

748
00:48:49,600 --> 00:48:53,400
She's not picking up. Probably no signal.

749
00:48:53,480 --> 00:48:55,120
The signal doesn't reach there.

750
00:48:56,600 --> 00:48:59,200
It's impressive that she went alone.

751
00:49:01,920 --> 00:49:02,760
She's brave.

752
00:49:13,960 --> 00:49:15,000
- Rok.
- Yes?

753
00:49:15,600 --> 00:49:17,080
- I'm going to the restroom.
- Okay.

754
00:49:19,080 --> 00:49:20,360
- Hey.
- What?

755
00:49:20,440 --> 00:49:21,960
Why does he keep talking about Pie?

756
00:49:22,040 --> 00:49:23,800
Does he have feelings for her?

757
00:49:25,360 --> 00:49:26,760
I don't know.

758
00:49:26,840 --> 00:49:29,400
Maybe because she's my best friend.

759
00:49:29,480 --> 00:49:32,480
And I tell him about her a lot.

760
00:49:32,560 --> 00:49:33,840
He probably just asks about her.

761
00:49:33,920 --> 00:49:36,320
Then stop talking about her.

762
00:49:36,400 --> 00:49:38,440
Talk about me instead.

763
00:49:38,520 --> 00:49:39,800
The good stuff, okay?

764
00:49:39,880 --> 00:49:41,880
So he can get to know me better.

765
00:49:46,080 --> 00:49:48,520
Hold the handlebars tight.
Sit up straight.

766
00:49:48,600 --> 00:49:50,640
Don't tense up. Look ahead.

767
00:49:50,720 --> 00:49:54,160
Life is a mindful adventure. Go!

768
00:49:55,240 --> 00:49:56,360
Okay.

769
00:49:56,440 --> 00:50:00,120
Tight grip. Sit up straight.
Don't tense up.

770
00:50:01,000 --> 00:50:03,760
Stay focused. Okay. Go!

771
00:50:06,120 --> 00:50:07,240
Hold tight!

772
00:50:07,320 --> 00:50:10,640
Tight grip, straight back. Don't tense up.

773
00:50:10,720 --> 00:50:12,120
Okay, okay!

774
00:50:12,200 --> 00:50:14,240
- Look ahead!
- Okay!

775
00:50:14,320 --> 00:50:15,600
Hold tight.

776
00:50:16,880 --> 00:50:17,960
I'm doing it!

777
00:50:18,040 --> 00:50:19,920
Win, I'm doing it!

778
00:50:20,000 --> 00:50:21,000
- I'm doing it!
- Yeah.

779
00:50:24,840 --> 00:50:25,680
I did it!

780
00:50:29,200 --> 00:50:30,920
- Sorry.
- It's okay.

781
00:50:35,560 --> 00:50:36,520
Not bad, right?

782
00:50:54,760 --> 00:50:57,280
You don't have to take me. I can go alone.

783
00:50:57,800 --> 00:51:00,080
I'm not taking you.
Just wanted a change of scenery.

784
00:51:00,160 --> 00:51:02,840
I've never met the Pga K'nyau before.
Let me come along.

785
00:51:04,120 --> 00:51:05,120
Suit yourself.

786
00:51:13,960 --> 00:51:15,000
Hey!

787
00:51:15,080 --> 00:51:16,440
- Wait for me!
- Catch up!

788
00:51:16,520 --> 00:51:17,520
Hey, wait!

789
00:51:27,440 --> 00:51:28,360
Win!

790
00:51:30,760 --> 00:51:32,000
We're here.

791
00:51:32,520 --> 00:51:33,680
Yes!

792
00:51:34,800 --> 00:51:36,160
BAAN HUAY TONG KOR

793
00:51:38,400 --> 00:51:40,120
Hello, Village Chief.

794
00:51:40,200 --> 00:51:41,280
Hello.

795
00:51:41,360 --> 00:51:43,360
I'm Pie, Professor Phupha's student.

796
00:51:44,000 --> 00:51:45,080
Professor Phupha's student.

797
00:51:45,160 --> 00:51:47,880
He told me about you.

798
00:51:49,000 --> 00:51:50,480
Make yourself at home.

799
00:53:29,440 --> 00:53:30,560
You can draw too?

800
00:53:33,680 --> 00:53:36,000
It's nice. You like rainbows?

801
00:53:37,920 --> 00:53:39,400
Who doesn't?

802
00:53:40,320 --> 00:53:43,160
The best thing after rain is a rainbow.

803
00:53:43,800 --> 00:53:47,040
Seven colors lined up in the sky
out of nowhere.

804
00:53:47,120 --> 00:53:48,760
It's magical.

805
00:53:55,240 --> 00:53:57,240
It's just light refraction.

806
00:53:58,520 --> 00:53:59,360
What?

807
00:54:00,320 --> 00:54:02,600
You're not romantic at all.

808
00:54:38,880 --> 00:54:39,920
What are you drawing?

809
00:54:42,600 --> 00:54:43,720
Hey!

810
00:54:44,240 --> 00:54:46,000
Double rainbow. That's a bad omen!

811
00:54:46,080 --> 00:54:47,160
What bad omen?

812
00:54:47,240 --> 00:54:49,720
A double rainbow means love.

813
00:54:49,800 --> 00:54:52,560
They say if you see one,

814
00:54:52,640 --> 00:54:55,000
people who once loved each other
will meet again.

815
00:54:56,120 --> 00:54:58,840
- That's real. I even did a report on it.
- Yeah?

816
00:54:58,920 --> 00:55:02,040
You're making that up. It means death.

817
00:55:02,120 --> 00:55:05,560
Legend says a double rainbow
guides the dead to heaven.

818
00:55:05,640 --> 00:55:07,280
- To heaven? This?
- Yeah.

819
00:55:07,360 --> 00:55:08,680
- Yes.
- Then that's good.

820
00:55:10,800 --> 00:55:13,920
Want to go to heaven? Go alone.
I'm not dying anytime soon.

821
00:55:16,960 --> 00:55:19,000
Here, take your bad omen.

822
00:55:19,520 --> 00:55:22,000
And move over. I'm working.

823
00:55:22,080 --> 00:55:23,440
- Move!
- Thank you.

824
00:56:01,080 --> 00:56:02,080
Hurry up!

825
00:56:02,760 --> 00:56:05,200
I'm coming. Wait for me!

826
00:56:05,280 --> 00:56:06,920
Hello.

827
00:56:07,960 --> 00:56:09,320
Hello!

828
00:56:09,880 --> 00:56:12,200
We use this…

829
00:56:30,040 --> 00:56:30,880
Eat up!

830
00:56:33,960 --> 00:56:35,920
<i>There was hot water left,</i>
<i>so I made this for you.</i>

831
00:56:36,000 --> 00:56:39,360
<i>It goes surprisingly well</i>
<i>with pork cracklings. Try it.</i>

832
00:56:43,840 --> 00:56:45,160
TEXTILE PATTERNS OF HUAY TONG KOR

833
00:56:48,880 --> 00:56:51,400
<i>Eat up. This place has been</i>
<i>Michelin-rated for three years.</i>

834
00:56:54,840 --> 00:56:55,840
You've got this!

835
00:57:17,960 --> 00:57:19,680
<i>I don't have much time left.</i>

836
00:57:19,760 --> 00:57:22,520
<i>I'd rather spend it</i>
<i>collecting as much happiness as I can.</i>

837
00:57:22,600 --> 00:57:25,000
Pie, are you seriously ill? Are you dying?

838
00:57:25,080 --> 00:57:28,040
I have to check on a hotel project
in Mae Hong Son.

839
00:57:28,600 --> 00:57:29,640
Want to come with me?

840
00:57:29,720 --> 00:57:31,880
<i>Maybe we met by coincidence.</i>

841
00:57:31,960 --> 00:57:33,840
But we'll stay together long enough

842
00:57:33,920 --> 00:57:35,800
<i>for it to become destiny.</i>

843
00:57:35,880 --> 00:57:37,080
<i>With comets,</i>

844
00:57:37,160 --> 00:57:41,800
<i>astronomers</i>
<i>can calculate when they’ll return.</i>

845
00:57:43,080 --> 00:57:44,200
<i>But with people,</i>

846
00:57:45,160 --> 00:57:47,760
you never know
when paths will cross again.

847
00:57:47,840 --> 00:57:50,520
They say, if you just wait,

848
00:57:50,600 --> 00:57:52,280
you might lose the chance forever.

849
00:58:22,360 --> 00:58:26,520
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
